      <TextArea layoutY="72.0" prefHeight="256.0" prefWidth="600.0" text="HOUSE AREA:&#10;You have a house, which you are required to provide with enough electricity.&#10;You have to provide the total amount of the electricity requirement, in order to move to the next year until you reach the year 2030, where the game ends. &#10;If you are not able to fulfill the requirement, and you are out of money, the game will also end.&#10;&#10;BUILD AREA:&#10;You have a property, where you can install wind turbines and solar panels, which you can buy in the shops in the game. &#10;&#10;SALARY:&#10;Each year you will receive a salary of approximately 300.000 DKK&#10;&#10;SHOPS:&#10;In the wind turbine shop you can buy 2 sizes of wind turbines, that generates electricity.&#10;&#10;In the solar shop you can buy 3 sizes of solar panels, that generates electricity.&#10;&#10;In the fossil shop you can buy electricity from external providers, who uses fossil fuels to generate electricity.&#10;&#10;In the battery shop you can buy 3 types of batteries, that can store some of the energy that your windmill(s) and/or solar panel(s) produce. &#10;&#10;In the retail shop an electric car and a heating pump, which can be powered by your excess electricity production and help you bring down your carbon footprint.    &#10;&#10;Remember that at the start of the game, you have a normal car that runs on petrol, and you are also     heating your house with gas, both resulting in an increased carbon footprint.&#10;&#10;EXCESS ENERGY:&#10;If you install enough windmills and/or solar panels you will be able to create excess energy which is automatically sold if not used and you will receive the payment.&#10;&#10;THE END OF THE GAME:  &#10;At the end of the game a recap page will be shown, where you can see your balance, your total excess energy production, your total CO2 emission and a score that shows your overall performance.    &#10;&#10;YOUR GOALS ARE:&#10;  -    Reach the end year 2030&#10;  -  